Even if she was washing the dishes,
Mme quand elle est en train de laver la vaiselle,
she would run and leave the dishes there
elle court et laisse les bols.
she would run and leave it there,
no matter whether day or night.
n'importe s'il est jour ou nuit.
And one day the hyenas where having a party,
agu druk mundumo araad buye ha fte ,
Puis un jour les hynes font une fte.
They were drumming, they drummed and drummed
Ils battaient les tambours, ils battaient fort.
At night the girl was sleeping,
but as she heard how they drummed she got up.
aussitt qu'elle entendait les battements elle s'est lev.
She thought maybe the villagers were having a dance.
ayen kati jamaa ka bukoor iraadi baa
Elle pense que c'taient peut-tre les gens du village qui faiaient la fte.
She got up and her mother told her: Dont go!
Elle se lve, sa mre lui dit de ne pas aller.
Elle suit les battements des tambour.
She got to where the hyenas were dancing
adk rek adelun kgini mundumo araane baa
Elle va jusqu' arriver l o les hynes dansent.
As soon as they saw her they said: Well, today we have meat.
awlem rek ayeni : yoo guug incooce ahar
Quand ils la voient ils disent: Bien, aujourd'hui on a de la viande!
We will have you for dinner tonight.
guug fi gigutimin buyaa ka diguguuu

The hyenas came to eat her.
Les hynes venaient pour la manger.
wait I'll dance when I finish eat me.
utu an ia gitijini apre uhbmu
attendez que je danse, et quand j'ai fini vous me mangez.
And the girl sang and sang
Et la fille chante et chante,
and while she sang she retreated
yin yin agu gyini aey bihuun
et en chantant elle se retire.

He saw with only one eye

And he said to his friends:
elle est en train de s'vader.

The one-eyed hyena said to his friends:
Mundum a sijil sisnduk ayen indinnkenem
L'hyne avec un seul oeil disait ses amis:
She is going, she is returning, soon she will have reached her house"

she went back, as she made one more step she saw her house,

She was entering, when one hyena grabbed her foot
agu buan rek mundum dinem alax sidikenem sisnduk

ayen indinnkenem umr apaxi aani a koonahanam

elle le prend Elle dit aux hynes:

even though the drums resounded, they were beating like that,
Evenfrom here to the house of Louise-Marie she wouldnt go.
